OL,3,CBarton House: Resident convicted of
OL,4,Ctheft has sentence reduced
OL,6,FThe fire alarms were found, he was
OL,7,Farrested initially on suspicion of
OL,8,Fhandling stolen goods, and later
OL,9,Fcharged with, and convicted of, theft.
OL,11,FMagistrates gave him 60 hours of
OL,12,Funpaid work as part of a 12-month
OL,13,Fcommunity order, along with costs and
OL,14,Fa victim surcharge totalling #85.
OL,16,FAt an appeal hearing held at Bristol
OL,17,FCrown Court on Thursday 1 August, the
OL,18,Ffather-of-two appealed against that
OL,19,Fsentence, not the conviction.
