OL,3,CBarton House: Resident convicted of
OL,4,Ctheft has sentence reduced
OL,6,F"His actions, while legally wrong,
OL,7,Fwhich he has shown cooperation and
OL,8,Fregret for at every stage, stemmed
OL,9,Ffrom a confluence of trauma,
OL,10,Fmedication side effects, intense
OL,11,Fpersonal and family pressures and a
OL,12,Fgenuine desire to protect his
OL,13,Fcommunity."
OL,15,FJudge Blair accepted Mr Ali's
OL,16,Fsubmissions and reduced the sentence
OL,17,Ffrom a 12-month community order with
OL,18,F60 hours unpaid work to a 12-month
OL,19,Fconditional discharge. The victim
OL,20,Fsurcharge and costs were also reduced
OL,21,Fto #26.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@KO]
